<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN1057E" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Display Grid</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN10582" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Displays or hides grid lines that you can use to align objects such as graphics on a page.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN10585" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Snap to Grid</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN10589" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Automatically aligns objects to vertical and horizontal grid lines. To override this feature, hold down the <switchinline select="sys"><caseinline select="MAC">Command key</caseinline><defaultinline>Ctrl key</defaultinline></switchinline> when you drag an object.<comment>UFI: copied from shared\optionen\01050100.xhp</comment></paragraph><comment>UFI removed GridFront help id</comment><paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN105C9" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Grid to Front</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN105CD" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW"><ahelp hid=".">Displays the grid lines in front of the objects on the slide or page.</ahelp></paragraph>
<section id="relatedtopics">
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id4372692" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Set the grid color on Tools - Options - %PRODUCTNAME - <link href="text/shared/optionen/01012000.xhp">Appearance</link>.</paragraph>
</section>
